<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 01:53:35 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>美国人将医疗保健费用、赤字、通货膨胀视为国家面临的大问题</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/05/11/americans-see-health-care-costs-deficit-inflation-as-big-problems-facing-the-nation/</link><description>经济问题继续主导美国人对国家首要问题的排名。与此同时，自特朗普第二任期开始以来，认为非法移民是一个非常大问题的比例有所下降。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 01:53:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/05/11/americans-see-health-care-costs-deficit-inflation-as-big-problems-facing-the-nation/</guid></item><item><title>关于在美国的古巴人的 10 个事实</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/07/10-facts-about-cubans-in-the-u-s/</link><description>数百万生活在美国的人的起源可以追溯到古巴。他们是美国第三大西班牙裔群体，仅次于墨西哥人和波多黎各人。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 01:53:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/07/10-facts-about-cubans-in-the-u-s/</guid></item><item><title>妈妈、教练、医生、企业家：谁是美国健康和保健的影响者？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/data-labs/2026/05/07/moms-coaches-doctors-entrepreneurs-who-are-americas-health-and-wellness-influencers/</link><description>一半 50 岁以下的美国成年人表示，他们从社交媒体影响者或播客中获取健康和保健信息。这些影响者中约有十分之四的人将自己描述为医疗保健专业人员；教练和企业家几乎同样常见。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 01:38:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/data-labs/2026/05/07/moms-coaches-doctors-entrepreneurs-who-are-americas-health-and-wellness-influencers/</guid></item><item><title>71% 的美国房主表示他们的房屋保险费用上涨</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/06/71-of-u-s-homeowners-say-their-home-insurance-costs-have-gone-up/</link><description>房主最常提到的两个原因是保险公司想要赚更多钱以及维修和重建的成本。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 01:50:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/06/71-of-u-s-homeowners-say-their-home-insurance-costs-have-gone-up/</guid></item><item><title>许多美国人认为公用事业公司要为其不断上涨的家庭能源费用负责</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/06/many-americans-hold-utility-companies-responsible-for-their-rising-home-energy-bills/</link><description>四分之三的美国成年人表示，近年来他们的家庭能源成本有所上涨，其中 42% 的人表示这些成本上涨了很多。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 01:35:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/06/many-americans-hold-utility-companies-responsible-for-their-rising-home-energy-bills/</guid></item><item><title>问题措辞如何影响同性恋道德民意调查</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/decoded/2026/05/06/how-question-wording-affects-polling-on-the-morality-of-homosexuality/</link><description>一项新的调查实验显示，美国人基本上不区分“同性恋”和“同性恋行为”的道德，尽管某些亚群体可能会这样做。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 01:20:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/decoded/2026/05/06/how-question-wording-affects-polling-on-the-morality-of-homosexuality/</guid></item><item><title>约一半美国人继续表示特朗普政府在驱逐出境问题上做得“太多”</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/04/about-half-of-americans-continue-to-say-trump-administration-is-doing-too-much-on-deportations/</link><description>认为政府在驱逐非法居住的移民方面做得太少的比例略有上升，这主要是由共和党人推动的。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 01:46:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/04/about-half-of-americans-continue-to-say-trump-administration-is-doing-too-much-on-deportations/</guid></item><item><title>随着支持率下滑，特朗普在多项个人特质上失势</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/05/01/trump-loses-ground-on-several-personal-traits-as-approval-rating-slips/</link><description>大多数美国人（56%）表示，在特朗普任期内，联邦政府的道德和诚实整体水平有所下降。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 May 2026 01:29:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/05/01/trump-loses-ground-on-several-personal-traits-as-approval-rating-slips/</guid></item><item><title>美国人仍然批评特朗普政府对伊朗的态度</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/01/americans-remain-critical-of-trump-administrations-approach-to-iran/</link><description>62%的美国人不赞成特朗普对伊朗军事行动的处理方式，59%的人表示美国在使用武力方面做出了错误的决定。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 02 May 2026 01:14:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/01/americans-remain-critical-of-trump-administrations-approach-to-iran/</guid></item><item><title>大多数美国人现在表示美国外交政策忽视其他国家的利益</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/28/most-americans-now-say-u-s-foreign-policy-ignores-the-interests-of-other-countries/</link><description>对于美国是否为和平做出贡献、是否考虑别国利益、是否赢得世界尊重，各党派存在不同看法。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 01:51:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/28/most-americans-now-say-u-s-foreign-policy-ignores-the-interests-of-other-countries/</guid></item></channel></rss>